        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-06T03:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-06T03:30:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Journal</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-06T09:30:00+01:00">October 6, 1946, 9:30 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> (PC) (Journal) 63</p>
                <p>The Commission met to review the <hi rend="italic">Rapporteur’s</hi> report to
                    the Plenary Conference.<note n="1" xml:id="d310fn1">For text of C.P.(Plen) Doc.
                        26, October 7, Report of the Economic Commission for Italy, see <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_338">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            338</ref>.</note> The report was approved subject to drafting changes
                    which might be communicated to the <hi rend="italic">Rapporteur</hi> by the
                    members. After adoption of a resolution of appreciation for the services of the
                    Chairman, Secretariat and <hi rend="italic">Rapporteur</hi>, proposed by Mr.
                        <persName>Thorp</persName>, the Commission adjourned <hi rend="italic">sine
                        die</hi>.</p>
            </div>
